body.description: Explore an intergalactic world as you scoop, discover, and use learning toys for 4 year olds to engage your senses with the Creativity for Kids Outer Space Sensory Bin.This self-contained space toy bin is an out-of-this-world sensory experience - just add imagination for an engaging creative, hands-on play activity for kids. Sensory bins allow toddlers to discover, imagine, learn and create while engaging their senses and having FUN! Scoop, sort, and explore in this self-contained sensory bin. Sensory bins have many toddler activities and learning benefits for kids to build fine motor skills, promote sensory development and encourage imaginative play. For easy cleanup, place your bin and toddler toys for boys and girls ages 3-4+ on a tablecloth and scoop, sort, dig, and build for endless hours of hands-on pretend play! All sensory bin fillers are carefully selected, and safety tested to provide the best at-home play activity. This complete space toys for kids ages 3-5+ play set includes 2.5 lbs of outer space rocks, tongs, scoop, and fun sensory bin fillers such as squishy alien, astronaut, foam planets, glow-in-the-dark stars, spirals, and sparkly pom poms all conveniently packed in bin with lid for easy storage (Bin measures approx. 14.5" W x 10.25" L x 4.75" H). Looking for preschool toy gift ideas? Sensory bins make great gifts for toddlers, birthday gifts, as well as kids gifts for any occasion! When you are done playing with the bin and toddler boy and girl toys, upcycle the bin, by planting flowers or storing small toys inside. You can also recycle the bin to do your part in saving our Earth. Since 1976, Creativity for Kids has proudly made fun and creative gifts for kids to nurture their confidence for life. The Creativity for Kids Sensory Bin Activity kit - Outer Space makes a great gift for 4 year old boys and girls! The sensory bin is recommended for toddlers ages 3-5+.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute but messy
reviews.reviewText: Super cute, love all the stuff in the bin for the kids to play with. However, I definitely should have read through the description better. The sand is like the super fine sand box sand and it’s so easy to get everywhere. The sensory sand that comes in like the construction set is much better BUT still definitely worth the buy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A Hit with a three year old boy
reviews.reviewText: My son, recently obsessive over construction equipment loved this gift for his birthday.Each day for a week he requested to play with his "construction site". He especially likes the sensory aspect of rolling the sand flat.Only cons I would say are the trucks are cheap and come apart easily, so we were subbing in some of his other cars and that the container is a little small so sand was getting out if he got too excited playing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not enough sand
reviews.reviewText: This was a “what Kristen bought” advertisement. I tried it because it was a good price. It looked like there was a small amount of sand in it so with such a great price, $12.00 each I ordered three.I’m glad I did because that’s what we needed to make this work.The sand is kenetic sand, which is kind of a sticky sand, that is a clean play, and great for a sensory feel. The rocks enclosed are pebbles that are a chocking hazard and the toys are cheap plastic. The shovel already broke after one play time. The tray with a lid is practical and nice to have but one out of three was damaged.It took three weeks to be delivered and the box looked like it had been tossed around a lot.I will replace the rocks with bigger ones and condense the sand into one storage bin.$36.00 for a bin of kenetic sand and a storage bin was worth it after all.My 3year old grand was excited to play with it.
